-- Shanghai shares hover around two-month lows, down 2.6 pct this week
-- By Alice Woodhouse
-- Fri Mar 14, 2014 03:09AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, March 14 (Reuters) - China shares fell and teetered around two-month lows on Friday, after online-payment-related companies slid as China's central bank called for halt to certain types of mobile payments.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended down 0.7 percent on the day at 2,004.33 points and declined 2.6 percent for the week.  The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings slipped 0.8 percent on the day, and 2.1 percent on the week.